# Citation metadata for Monadic Chat.
# Update `version` and `date-released` at each release (see docs_dev/release_procedure.md).
# A Zenodo DOI will be added under `doi:` when minted for the v1.0.0 tag.
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Monadic Chat in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "Monadic Chat"
abstract: >-
  Monadic Chat is a locally hosted web application for building and running
  AI chatbots that operate across multiple LLM providers within a reproducible,
  Docker-isolated Linux environment. It supports tool use, code execution, a
  local PDF/document knowledge base, voice interaction, image/video/audio
  analysis and generation, structured (monadic) conversation context, and
  AI-to-AI conversations, making it usable both as an application platform and
  as a framework for language research and education.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Hasebe"
    given-names: "Yoichiro"
    email: "yohasebe@gmail.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/yohasebe/monadic-chat"
url: "https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "1.0.0-beta.28"
date-released: "2026-07-13"
keywords:
  - large-language-models
  - multi-provider
  - reproducible-research
  - docker
  - retrieval-augmented-generation
  - conversational-ai
  - language-education
